This article discusses the official state visit of Prime Minister Modi of India to the United States. The visit highlights the strong relationship between the world's oldest and largest democracies. Education is a key focus of the visit, with both leaders recognizing its importance in preparing young people for the modern workforce. The article also mentions the partnership between universities in both countries, leading research, and creating apprenticeships and internships. The goal is to build a stronger bond between India and the United States and work together to create a better future for everyone.